2026-03-27T17:01:01.255Z JOY-0061 item.created "Integration test infrastructure with bats and trycmd" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-27T17:01:14.803Z JOY-0061 comment.added "Two-layer testing strategy for Joy CLI:\n\nLayer 1 -- bats (behavior): dynamic fixtures via joy CLI, tests flows and logic.\nLayer 2 -- trycmd (snapshots): static fixtures, tests exact output stability.\n\nWhen to use which:\n- New CLI command or flag: bats test for behavior\n- Output formatting change: trycmd snapshot\n- Customer journey / multi-step flow: bats\n- Exit code contract: bats\n- Both when a command has important output AND behavioral logic\n\nDirectory structure:\n  tests/cmd/           -- trycmd tests (.toml + .stdout + fixtures/)\n  tests/integration/   -- bats tests (.bats + setup.bash)\n\nJustfile recipes: test-cmd (trycmd), test-int (bats), test (all)\n\nAI rule: every new CLI command or flag must have at least one bats test. Output-critical commands also get a trycmd snapshot." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
